Plot / Synopsis

The Gift to Stalin is a film that tells the story of a little boy named Sasha who is sent to Kazakhstan. He is saved from death by an old Kazakh man, Kasym, who takes the boy to his home. The film is set in 1949. The title, The Gift to Stalin  has two significances. In 1949, the Soviet government carried out a nuclear test for the anniversary of Stalin's 70th birthday. Many innocent people fell the victims to the nuclear test. The other significance is about Sashka's dream. He hopes that if he gives Stalin a gift, he will be able to see his parents again, not knowing that they were killed. -- Wikipedia
